HEADWORD: juvenile hormone
<hw>juvenile hormone</hw> <fld>(Zo/'94l.)</fld> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
hormone secreted by insects which inhibits the molting of an insect from
its juvenile into its adult form; also, substances having similar
activity, but produced by plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juvenileness</ent>⟦br⟧
